==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excitation
<hw>Ex`ci*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excitatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>excitation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of exciting or putting in motion; the act of rousing up or
awakening.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The act of producing
excitement (stimulation); also, the excitement produced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excitative</ent>⟦br⟧
